WEBVTT

1
00:05:11.313 --> 00:05:13.270
Go past me children.

2
00:05:14.316 --> 00:05:16.398
There are some to my left

3
00:05:17.361 --> 00:05:18.601
and some ahead here.

4
00:06:44.197 --> 00:06:45.187
No.
-Yes.

5
00:06:45.324 --> 00:06:46.359
No.
-Yes.

6
00:06:47.743 --> 00:06:49.950
Sleep child sleep.

7
00:06:50.078 --> 00:06:52.194
Don't sit on me.

8
00:06:52.331 --> 00:06:53.492
I didn't sit on you.

9
00:06:55.125 --> 00:06:58.914
That's what happens
when you stamp on my foot.

10
00:08:01.566 --> 00:08:04.149
You'd better not throw a
bucket of water over me.

11
00:08:04.277 --> 00:08:05.938
No. we'd never do that.

12
00:08:06.279 --> 00:08:07.815
It better not make me late.

13
00:08:11.284 --> 00:08:13.275
This way... and out.

14
00:08:15.706 --> 00:08:17.367
Watch out for the steps.

15
00:08:18.083 --> 00:08:20.745
Feel for it... and down. Perfect.

16
00:08:24.256 --> 00:08:27.044
Last step. and now turn around.

17
00:08:27.467 --> 00:08:29.879
There you go. Wait. Stand here.

18
00:08:33.265 --> 00:08:34.926
Surprise.

19
00:08:36.184 --> 00:08:37.720
Is this for me?
-Yes.

20
00:08:39.271 --> 00:08:41.558
Thank you.
-Happy birthday.

21
00:08:42.649 --> 00:08:43.980
Where did you get it?

22
00:08:44.109 --> 00:08:45.395
I have my sources.

23
00:08:46.319 --> 00:08:48.401
One. two. three passengers.

24
00:08:48.530 --> 00:08:50.362
Who wants the first ride?
-Me.

25
00:08:52.659 --> 00:08:55.242
You.
You can have the first ride.

26
00:08:58.582 --> 00:09:00.368
The paint is still fresh.

27
00:09:00.500 --> 00:09:03.242
Annagret will have a green bottom.

28
00:09:25.275 --> 00:09:26.765
Coats. bags. off to school.

29
00:09:26.902 --> 00:09:28.108
Thank you children.

30
00:09:31.239 --> 00:09:32.274
Goodbye.

31
00:09:35.535 --> 00:09:37.617
Inge. pull your socks up.

32
00:09:47.547 --> 00:09:50.380
Bye-bye Daddy.

33
00:10:10.904 --> 00:10:12.315
Phlox.

34
00:10:24.835 --> 00:10:26.496
Would you like to smell a rose?

35
00:10:27.337 --> 00:10:30.625
Smell a rose. Yes. This one.

36
00:10:34.427 --> 00:10:35.713
This one is beautiful.

37
00:10:47.107 --> 00:10:49.724
Look. what a big dahlia.

38
00:10:52.279 --> 00:10:56.694
And a ladybird. Yes.

39
00:12:30.752 --> 00:12:31.742
Bronek.

40
00:12:49.312 --> 00:12:50.347
Marta.

41
00:12:55.443 --> 00:12:56.478
Upstairs please.

42
00:12:56.611 --> 00:12:58.727
Then come and see me.

43
00:13:01.241 --> 00:13:02.231
Sophie.

44
00:13:05.704 --> 00:13:06.785
Aniela. come.

45
00:13:18.049 --> 00:13:20.416
Choose something you like. Only one each.

46
00:13:20.552 --> 00:13:22.088
Take something.
-Thank you.

47
00:14:28.578 --> 00:14:30.410
This one needs to be cleaned

48
00:14:30.538 --> 00:14:32.495
and the lining has to be mended.

49
00:14:32.624 --> 00:14:34.581
Be careful with it.
-Of course.

50
00:14:35.001 --> 00:14:36.412
Go back downstairs.

51
00:15:47.740 --> 00:15:49.606
The bees are flying.

52
00:15:50.160 --> 00:15:52.527
It is hot. isn't it?

53
00:15:52.912 --> 00:15:54.073
How was your journey?

54
00:15:54.914 --> 00:15:57.622
Long. But we're here now.

55
00:15:57.750 --> 00:15:59.787
Yes indeed. So. not too bad?

56
00:16:00.086 --> 00:16:01.247
No. not too bad.

57
00:16:02.130 --> 00:16:03.871
Easier than last time actually.

58
00:16:04.299 --> 00:16:07.212
Excellent. Well then. welcome back.

59
00:16:07.719 --> 00:16:09.756
Absolutely. We're glad to be here.

60
00:16:10.930 --> 00:16:13.638
Should we take our shoes off as well?
-No.

61
00:16:14.267 --> 00:16:16.679
Did you travel via Prague or Vienna?

62
00:16:17.353 --> 00:16:21.438
Prague. It is 56 minutes faster.

63
00:16:47.800 --> 00:16:49.211
She asked me where I got

64
00:16:49.344 --> 00:16:50.630
one of my jackets from.

65
00:16:50.762 --> 00:16:51.968
I said. "Canada."

66
00:16:52.096 --> 00:16:54.428
And she asked. "How did you get to Canada?"

67
00:16:55.141 --> 00:16:57.599
She thought you meant the country?
-Of course.

68
00:16:57.727 --> 00:16:59.217
An understandable mistake.

69
00:16:59.354 --> 00:17:02.722
The same thing happened
when Helga Pattisch came for the first time.

70
00:17:02.857 --> 00:17:06.145
Out of all of the clothes. she chose a dress

71
00:17:06.277 --> 00:17:10.236
that belonged to some little
Jewess half her size.

72
00:17:10.365 --> 00:17:13.528
I could only pull the zipper up to here.

73
00:17:13.660 --> 00:17:14.991
and the dress came apart.

74
00:17:15.119 --> 00:17:17.235
And I pulled and pulled at it.

75
00:17:17.372 --> 00:17:20.910
She just looked down at herself and said.

76
00:17:21.042 --> 00:17:22.749
"I love this dress."

77
00:17:22.877 --> 00:17:24.663
In the end she took it.

78
00:17:24.796 --> 00:17:27.754
And she said. "I'll go on a diet."

79
00:17:31.719 --> 00:17:34.507
Would you like more coffee?
-Yes please. Thank you.

80
00:17:37.725 --> 00:17:40.137
You take it black?
-Black is good. thank you.

81
00:17:43.606 --> 00:17:45.813
Helga's husband only adopted

82
00:17:45.942 --> 00:17:49.355
that little Polish boy to keep her at home.

83
00:17:52.031 --> 00:17:53.487
That's what she told me.

84
00:17:55.034 --> 00:17:57.947
And he hits her as well.

85
00:17:58.079 --> 00:18:00.571
I didn't know that.
-How do you know that?

86
00:18:00.957 --> 00:18:04.495
Haven't you noticed the bruises on her arms?

87
00:18:05.795 --> 00:18:07.786
I forgot to tell you something.

88
00:18:08.214 --> 00:18:11.798
Guess where I found this diamond?

89
00:18:12.552 --> 00:18:14.042
In the toothpaste.

90
00:18:14.178 --> 00:18:15.634
No. Really?

91
00:18:15.930 --> 00:18:17.512
How clever you must have to be.

92
00:18:17.640 --> 00:18:19.051
Yes. they are very clever.

93
00:18:19.183 --> 00:18:22.141
I've ordered more toothpaste
because you never know.

94
00:18:40.872 --> 00:18:43.910
I think I told you about
the Schilling concert.

95
00:18:44.042 --> 00:18:46.659
About Brigitte Frank's ermine fur coat.

96
00:18:46.794 --> 00:18:50.003
Did I tell you about it?
-I don't think so.

97
00:18:50.131 --> 00:18:51.166
Look.

98
00:18:53.343 --> 00:18:54.879
She looks like an empress.

99
00:18:55.470 --> 00:18:58.132
The other side of it is the next chamber

100
00:18:58.264 --> 00:19:02.132
with the next load ready to burn

101
00:19:02.268 --> 00:19:04.225
once the pieces here

102
00:19:04.354 --> 00:19:07.346
have been completely incinerated.

103
00:19:07.440 --> 00:19:08.646
How long does it take?

104
00:19:08.775 --> 00:19:12.018
7 hours. 400 to 500 at a time.

105
00:19:12.153 --> 00:19:13.643
Closer to 500.

106
00:19:13.863 --> 00:19:15.979
So. once that has happened.

107
00:19:16.115 --> 00:19:19.358
you close this chimney.

108
00:19:19.494 --> 00:19:21.781
then simultaneously open the next.

109
00:19:21.913 --> 00:19:24.655
The fire will follow the air.

110
00:19:24.791 --> 00:19:27.624
through this baffle of course.

111
00:19:27.752 --> 00:19:31.370
into this chamber and then burn this load.

112
00:19:32.507 --> 00:19:36.967
The chamber directly opposite
the combustion zone.

113
00:19:37.470 --> 00:19:40.258
which burns at roughly 1.000 degrees.

114
00:19:40.765 --> 00:19:47.728
has by now cooled to around 40 degrees.

115
00:19:47.855 --> 00:19:49.437
Cool enough to unload the ash

116
00:19:49.857 --> 00:19:52.064
and then reload the chamber.

117
00:19:52.485 --> 00:19:54.192
So. this chamber is cooling

118
00:19:54.320 --> 00:19:55.810
while this one is heating up?

119
00:19:55.947 --> 00:20:00.908
Correct. The process moves one chamber over.

120
00:20:01.035 --> 00:20:02.651
counterclockwise.

121
00:20:02.995 --> 00:20:07.990
So. burn. cool. unload. reload.

122
00:20:08.418 --> 00:20:09.408
And...

123
00:20:10.336 --> 00:20:11.667
Continuously.

124
00:20:23.850 --> 00:20:24.931
Cheers.

125
00:20:28.062 --> 00:20:29.052
Dilla.

126
00:20:33.109 --> 00:20:34.770
Happy birthday. Commandant.

127
00:20:36.571 --> 00:20:38.437
Happy birthday. Commandant.

128
00:20:38.573 --> 00:20:40.860
It is an honour to serve under you.

129
00:20:40.992 --> 00:20:42.073
Thank you.

130
00:20:42.827 --> 00:20:44.317
Happy birthday. Commandant.

131
00:20:44.454 --> 00:20:45.489
Thank you.

132
00:20:45.747 --> 00:20:47.454
Happy birthday. Commandant.

133
00:20:48.040 --> 00:20:49.075
Thank you.

134
00:20:50.168 --> 00:20:51.784
That is a rifle.

135
00:20:52.462 --> 00:20:55.250
And this is also a rifle.

136
00:20:55.673 --> 00:20:58.882
And here is one with a pistol.

137
00:20:59.010 --> 00:21:01.172
and another rifle here.

138
00:21:24.243 --> 00:21:25.233
Do you hear that?

139
00:21:26.496 --> 00:21:30.831
It's a bittern. A heron.
A Eurasian grey heron.

140
00:22:06.452 --> 00:22:09.911
You cried like this too.

141
00:22:10.414 --> 00:22:12.280
You were even louder.

142
00:22:14.085 --> 00:22:16.042
What's going on with her?

143
00:22:16.170 --> 00:22:17.626
She's strong. isn't she?

144
00:22:20.258 --> 00:22:22.124
I'd like to try mine now.

145
00:23:33.581 --> 00:23:34.992
What are you doing?

146
00:23:36.375 --> 00:23:37.410
What are you doing?

147
00:23:37.543 --> 00:23:38.578
I'm looking.

148
00:23:39.170 --> 00:23:40.251
At what?

149
00:23:40.713 --> 00:23:41.748
Teeth.

150
00:23:49.889 --> 00:23:51.050
What are you doing?

151
00:23:51.474 --> 00:23:52.555
Nothing.

152
00:26:14.617 --> 00:26:15.948
What are you doing here?

153
00:26:16.786 --> 00:26:18.402
I'm handing out sugar.

154
00:26:19.371 --> 00:26:20.406
Who to?

155
00:26:21.290 --> 00:26:22.496
I'm looking.

156
00:26:26.462 --> 00:26:27.452
Come.

157
00:26:42.144 --> 00:26:46.103
Then. a little white bird flew past

158
00:26:46.190 --> 00:26:49.603
to guide them out of the forest.

159
00:26:50.820 --> 00:26:52.606
Soon they arrived at a huge lake.

160
00:26:52.738 --> 00:26:56.197
They were puzzled as they
did not know how to cross it.

161
00:26:57.118 --> 00:27:01.954
Suddenly. a big beautiful swan
came swimming towards them

162
00:27:03.290 --> 00:27:05.952
"Oh beautiful swan. please be our boat."

163
00:27:06.752 --> 00:27:10.746
The swan bent its neck and came to the shore.

164
00:27:35.990 --> 00:27:37.651
Bracht phoned the house.

165
00:27:39.118 --> 00:27:41.701
Yes. while you were outside for your toast.

166
00:27:41.871 --> 00:27:45.205
I forgot to tell you.
He said he'd call back tomorrow. midday.

167
00:27:51.422 --> 00:27:52.583
Rudolf.

168
00:27:55.342 --> 00:27:58.380
Will you take me to that spa in Italy again?

169
00:28:02.641 --> 00:28:04.473
All that pampering.

170
00:28:06.187 --> 00:28:10.101
And the walks. And that nice couple we met.

171
00:28:16.530 --> 00:28:19.192
Is she wandering around again?
-No.

172
00:28:21.285 --> 00:28:22.616
And that man

173
00:28:24.371 --> 00:28:26.738
who played the accordion to the cows?

174
00:28:27.750 --> 00:28:28.990
They loved it.

175
00:28:29.585 --> 00:28:32.122
It was so funny.

176
00:28:33.214 --> 00:28:35.080
All looking at him like this.

177
00:28:43.474 --> 00:28:44.555
Will you?

178
00:28:45.184 --> 00:28:47.676
What?
-Well. take me back there.

179
00:28:48.145 --> 00:28:49.431
Yes.
-When?

180
00:28:51.398 --> 00:28:52.638
I don't know when.

181
00:28:59.490 --> 00:29:00.776
You smell nice.

182
00:29:02.493 --> 00:29:03.779
It's French.

183
00:29:16.966 --> 00:29:18.456
Oink. oink.

184
00:29:33.482 --> 00:29:37.225
Chocolate. If you see it. Any goodies.

185
00:30:17.901 --> 00:30:21.735
To the head of the Party Chancellery
Reichsleiter Bormann.

186
00:30:21.864 --> 00:30:22.899
Personal.

187
00:30:23.449 --> 00:30:24.780
Dear Reichsleiter

188
00:30:26.201 --> 00:30:29.944
I have learned that the commandant
of the gigantic K.L. Auschwitz

189
00:30:30.080 --> 00:30:31.616
Obersturmbannführer Höss

190
00:30:31.874 --> 00:30:33.160
also well known to you.

191
00:30:33.292 --> 00:30:34.657
is to be transferred.

192
00:30:35.252 --> 00:30:37.994
Comrade Höss has made
unprecedented achievements

193
00:30:38.130 --> 00:30:40.121
over four years of painstaking work.

194
00:30:40.257 --> 00:30:43.716
I witnessed the construction
of this great camp close up

195
00:30:43.844 --> 00:30:45.505
so can attest.

196
00:30:46.013 --> 00:30:50.928
Reichsführer Himmler himself acknowledges
the uniqueness of what he built.

197
00:30:51.810 --> 00:30:54.393
Now it is said that the
task is too big for him

198
00:30:54.521 --> 00:30:57.263
and that someone must take his place.

199
00:30:58.108 --> 00:31:00.566
Höss knows prisoner use inside out

200
00:31:01.236 --> 00:31:04.354
has close contacts with the
Silesian armaments industry

201
00:31:04.490 --> 00:31:08.154
and has brought groundbreaking ideas
to the whole field of KL practice.

202
00:31:08.285 --> 00:31:12.153
He is a model settler farmer
and an exemplary German pioneer of the East.

203
00:31:12.539 --> 00:31:15.497
His particular strength
is turning theory into practice.

204
00:31:15.626 --> 00:31:17.958
I will refrain from listing more qualities

205
00:31:18.087 --> 00:31:21.330
which prove a change in his
command is not possible.

206
00:31:22.007 --> 00:31:23.839
Therefore. could you please speak

207
00:31:23.967 --> 00:31:28.427
to the Reichsführer as soon as possible
to prevent the transfer of Comrade Höss.

208
00:31:29.098 --> 00:31:32.887
I would be very grateful for a brief reply.
Heil Hitler.

209
00:31:33.018 --> 00:31:34.725
Gauleiter Fritz Bracht.

210
00:31:39.691 --> 00:31:41.682
Can I do it now?
-In a moment.

211
00:31:43.987 --> 00:31:45.944
Did you know that storks

212
00:31:46.073 --> 00:31:47.438
fly as far as Africa?

213
00:31:48.826 --> 00:31:50.408
How far do you think they fly?

214
00:31:50.536 --> 00:31:53.073
How many kilometres?
-300?

215
00:31:53.455 --> 00:31:54.616
More.

216
00:32:11.265 --> 00:32:12.596
All these weeds here.

217
00:32:15.727 --> 00:32:17.889
You are what you say.

218
00:32:18.147 --> 00:32:19.387
You are what you say.

219
00:32:19.523 --> 00:32:23.437
Cows find this funny. The whole farm
is roaring. because you are so boring.

220
00:32:23.569 --> 00:32:24.684
Cows find this funny.

221
00:32:24.820 --> 00:32:27.278
The whole farm is roaring.
because you are so boring.

222
00:32:27.406 --> 00:32:28.988
No. you're boring.

223
00:33:20.584 --> 00:33:21.665
Come out.

224
00:33:45.901 --> 00:33:46.936
All is well.

225
00:33:48.362 --> 00:33:49.602
I hate you.

226
00:33:49.738 --> 00:33:53.072
Keep your eyes closed. or it'll hurt.
-I know.

227
00:33:53.200 --> 00:33:56.568
Once more. All good. Come here.

228
00:34:25.857 --> 00:34:28.019
We have to rinse your eyes.

229
00:34:28.151 --> 00:34:29.937
Everything's fine. You'll live.

230
00:34:39.454 --> 00:34:42.697
...with which 60.000 Italian spectators

231
00:34:42.833 --> 00:34:45.541
showered their victorious national team.

232
00:34:46.128 --> 00:34:49.120
We will be able to share in their delight.

233
00:34:49.965 --> 00:34:51.922
How long it's been since Milan saw

234
00:34:52.050 --> 00:34:54.132
their beloved Squadra Azzurra?

235
00:34:54.261 --> 00:34:57.344
And now they have returned with a 4-0 victory

236
00:34:57.514 --> 00:35:00.222
to the arena of their many triumphs.

237
00:35:00.851 --> 00:35:03.764
Can you imagine the celebration?

238
00:35:03.895 --> 00:35:06.683
4-0 against their old rivals Spain.

239
00:35:06.815 --> 00:35:09.807
who are again aspiring to a position of power

240
00:35:09.943 --> 00:35:11.559
in European football.

241
00:35:11.695 --> 00:35:14.813
as we Germans saw with our own eyes

242
00:35:14.948 --> 00:35:16.484
in Berlin last Sunday.

243
00:35:17.117 --> 00:35:19.575
But don't let the result fool you.

244
00:35:19.911 --> 00:35:22.198
4-0 was the final score.

245
00:35:22.331 --> 00:35:23.787
But at half time

246
00:35:23.915 --> 00:35:27.783
this thrilling Italian-Spanish encounter

247
00:35:27.919 --> 00:35:29.159
stood at O-0.

248
00:35:29.796 --> 00:35:30.786
Hang up.

249
00:35:35.761 --> 00:35:36.751
Fritz.

250
00:35:38.805 --> 00:35:39.795
Go on.

251
00:35:42.684 --> 00:35:44.095
What does it say?

252
00:35:54.655 --> 00:35:55.645
Well.

253
00:35:57.282 --> 00:35:59.899
No. you wrote a very powerful
letter on my behalf.

254
00:36:00.035 --> 00:36:02.026
Their minds were obviously made up.

255
00:36:03.955 --> 00:36:05.320
I'd better tell my wife.

256
00:36:09.878 --> 00:36:10.868
She might.

257
00:36:11.838 --> 00:36:13.829
The train stopped for ages at Krakow.

258
00:36:13.965 --> 00:36:14.955
How frustrating.

259
00:36:16.885 --> 00:36:18.501
And it was so hot.

260
00:36:19.096 --> 00:36:22.384
A lady fainted next to me. it was that hot.

261
00:36:23.141 --> 00:36:27.305
She's moving here with her husband.
who's an engineer. He's a lot older.

262
00:36:27.646 --> 00:36:30.388
Yes.
-They've both got jobs at a new factory.

263
00:36:30.524 --> 00:36:33.141
Siemens.
-Ah. yes. That's possible.

264
00:36:34.528 --> 00:36:38.817
All the big companies are here. he said.

265
00:36:38.949 --> 00:36:40.235
Yes. yes.

266
00:36:41.326 --> 00:36:44.535
Don't you need to get on?

267
00:36:44.663 --> 00:36:46.028
Yes. I'd better.

268
00:36:46.164 --> 00:36:47.996
I'll show Mum to the girls' room.

269
00:36:52.462 --> 00:36:53.827
Are you ready?

270
00:36:54.214 --> 00:36:55.875
You'll have Heidetraud's bed

271
00:36:56.007 --> 00:36:57.793
and she'll get in with Inge-Brigitte.

272
00:36:57.926 --> 00:37:00.213
You don't mind. do you?
-Of course not.

273
00:37:00.470 --> 00:37:03.053
The house looks big. but it actually isn't.

274
00:37:03.181 --> 00:37:04.763
The first thing we did

275
00:37:04.891 --> 00:37:07.303
was install central heating.

276
00:37:07.436 --> 00:37:11.395
It gets so cold in winter.

277
00:37:11.523 --> 00:37:12.979
You wouldn't believe it.

278
00:37:27.873 --> 00:37:28.988
Hand-painted.

279
00:37:29.124 --> 00:37:30.580
Really?
-Yes.

280
00:37:40.969 --> 00:37:43.131
This is Heidetraud's bed here.

281
00:37:43.805 --> 00:37:46.092
This is lovely.

282
00:37:46.767 --> 00:37:47.802
Truly.

283
00:37:50.103 --> 00:37:51.889
Such a lovely room.

284
00:37:52.439 --> 00:37:56.057
The top two drawers are for you.

285
00:37:56.318 --> 00:37:58.309
Yes. that's more than enough.

286
00:37:59.488 --> 00:38:00.899
Such beautiful flowers.

287
00:38:10.165 --> 00:38:11.451
Yes. try it.

288
00:38:12.250 --> 00:38:15.618
But I'm sleeping here?
-Yes. but they're both...

289
00:38:17.255 --> 00:38:18.416
...the same.

290
00:38:25.514 --> 00:38:26.504
My girl.

291
00:38:26.807 --> 00:38:30.095
That's spinach strudel. apple strudel.
potato salad.

292
00:38:30.602 --> 00:38:32.388
And your cinnamon rolls.

293
00:38:32.813 --> 00:38:34.019
My recipe?

294
00:38:40.737 --> 00:38:41.977
Very nice.

295
00:38:42.489 --> 00:38:43.479
My god.

296
00:38:44.741 --> 00:38:46.197
Subject:

297
00:38:46.326 --> 00:38:49.409
Lilac bushes by the commandant's
guard barracks.

298
00:38:53.375 --> 00:38:56.367
From now on. SS members who pick lilacs

299
00:38:57.712 --> 00:39:04.004
in a thoughtless and blatant manner

300
00:39:05.428 --> 00:39:07.419
so that the bushes bleed

301
00:39:08.473 --> 00:39:10.430
will be punished.

302
00:39:13.144 --> 00:39:14.509
I expect the SS members.

303
00:39:14.646 --> 00:39:17.388
if they wish to take some.

304
00:39:19.234 --> 00:39:20.599
to do it in a way

305
00:39:20.735 --> 00:39:22.476
that does not damage the bushes.

306
00:39:24.865 --> 00:39:27.903
In the interest of our whole community.

307
00:39:28.034 --> 00:39:29.616
I hope you understand

308
00:39:31.204 --> 00:39:32.569
that the lilac bushes

309
00:39:33.456 --> 00:39:35.538
are intended to decorate our entire camp

310
00:39:35.667 --> 00:39:38.785
both now and in the future.

311
00:39:41.631 --> 00:39:43.622
Jews in the house?

312
00:39:44.551 --> 00:39:47.009
The Jews are over the other side of the wall.

313
00:39:47.137 --> 00:39:48.377
They're local girls.

314
00:39:49.180 --> 00:39:50.511
Say hello to grandma.

315
00:39:53.310 --> 00:39:54.471
Hello.

316
00:39:58.189 --> 00:39:59.350
My God.

317
00:40:00.317 --> 00:40:04.857
He's got so big. and you have such nice hair.

318
00:40:06.698 --> 00:40:09.110
I think it's your turn to push.
isn't it Hans?

319
00:40:09.242 --> 00:40:12.030
Inge pushed you before
and now it's your turn. Go on.

320
00:40:12.454 --> 00:40:13.444
Let's go.

321
00:40:19.836 --> 00:40:21.418
This is all us.

322
00:40:22.631 --> 00:40:23.962
There's a grape vine.

323
00:40:24.758 --> 00:40:26.374
Obviously. it'll grow.

324
00:40:37.187 --> 00:40:38.677
It's huge.

325
00:40:39.606 --> 00:40:41.222
I'm speechless.

326
00:40:42.859 --> 00:40:44.816
It's all my design.

327
00:40:44.945 --> 00:40:50.236
All the planting and everything.
The greenhouse. the gazebo at the end.

328
00:40:50.367 --> 00:40:52.358
Is that a pool?
-Yes.

329
00:40:52.911 --> 00:40:55.198
I have gardeners. I couldn't do it alone.

330
00:40:55.330 --> 00:40:56.661
With a slide?
-Yes.

331
00:40:56.790 --> 00:40:57.825
Oh Heddy.

332
00:40:59.918 --> 00:41:01.033
Do you like it?

333
00:41:01.503 --> 00:41:04.586
Of course I like it. How could I not?

334
00:41:06.466 --> 00:41:09.925
This was a field three years ago.

335
00:41:11.262 --> 00:41:12.377
No.

336
00:41:14.057 --> 00:41:19.018
We just had the lower garden by the street.
And the house had a flat roof.

337
00:41:19.145 --> 00:41:21.352
It's hard to believe.

338
00:41:23.817 --> 00:41:25.979
And that's the camp wall?

339
00:41:26.111 --> 00:41:27.647
Yes. that's the camp wall.

340
00:41:27.779 --> 00:41:30.237
We planted more vines at the back

341
00:41:30.365 --> 00:41:32.276
to grow and cover it.

342
00:41:32.951 --> 00:41:34.988
Maybe Esther Silberman is over there.

343
00:41:35.120 --> 00:41:37.578
Which one was she?
-The one I used to clean for.

344
00:41:38.248 --> 00:41:40.580
She was the one who had the book readings.

345
00:41:41.543 --> 00:41:43.409
God knows what they were up to.

346
00:41:43.712 --> 00:41:44.873
Bolshevik stuff.

347
00:41:45.422 --> 00:41:46.457
Jewish stuff.

348
00:41:47.632 --> 00:41:50.750
And I got outbid on her curtains

349
00:41:50.885 --> 00:41:53.047
at the street auction.

350
00:41:53.388 --> 00:41:54.924
Her opposite. she got them.

351
00:41:55.432 --> 00:41:57.264
I loved those curtains.

352
00:41:59.436 --> 00:42:01.894
These flowers are so beautiful.

353
00:42:02.439 --> 00:42:03.850
The azaleas there.

354
00:42:04.482 --> 00:42:05.972
There are also vegetables.

355
00:42:06.776 --> 00:42:11.862
A few herbs. Rosemary.
Beetroot. This is fennel.

356
00:42:12.574 --> 00:42:14.156
Sunflowers.

357
00:42:18.163 --> 00:42:22.953
And here is kohlrabi. The
children love to eat it.

358
00:42:23.418 --> 00:42:27.787
Cabbage. Kale. Runner beans.

359
00:42:28.965 --> 00:42:30.000
Pumpkins.

360
00:42:30.884 --> 00:42:32.249
Potatoes and more.

361
00:42:38.767 --> 00:42:42.726
We have bees over here to provide our honey.

362
00:42:43.438 --> 00:42:44.803
It's a paradise garden.

363
00:42:46.608 --> 00:42:48.098
And Rudolf is okay?

364
00:42:48.234 --> 00:42:49.941
Yes. he's fine.

365
00:42:50.278 --> 00:42:53.270
Working non-stop. even when he's home.

366
00:42:54.532 --> 00:42:55.897
Which he loves.

367
00:42:57.077 --> 00:42:58.613
He's a busy bee.

368
00:42:58.745 --> 00:43:00.611
He is. Non-stop.

369
00:43:00.747 --> 00:43:03.705
And under pressure like you wouldn't believe.

370
00:43:06.669 --> 00:43:08.034
And you're okay?

371
00:43:10.423 --> 00:43:11.538
Do I look okay?

372
00:43:19.766 --> 00:43:22.303
Rudi calls me the Queen of Auschwitz.

373
00:43:32.445 --> 00:43:33.480
Honestly.

374
00:43:33.613 --> 00:43:36.275
To have all this.

375
00:43:40.745 --> 00:43:43.328
You really have landed on your feet. my child.

376
00:43:47.293 --> 00:43:49.375
The linden trees are turning yellow.

377
00:43:50.421 --> 00:43:53.038
It smelled so nice when they were flowering.

378
00:43:57.262 --> 00:43:59.629
This will grow and cover everything.

379
00:44:00.807 --> 00:44:02.923
You'll see next time you visit.

380
00:44:07.814 --> 00:44:08.770
No.

381
00:44:12.152 --> 00:44:13.142
Stop it.

382
00:45:23.181 --> 00:45:28.597
The heartfelt time we spent in the Höss house

383
00:45:29.646 --> 00:45:32.684
will always be

384
00:45:32.815 --> 00:45:37.434
among our most beautiful holiday memories.

385
00:45:37.570 --> 00:45:39.937
In the East lies our tomorrow.

386
00:45:40.698 --> 00:45:45.909
Thanks for your National Socialist hospitality.

387
00:45:47.121 --> 00:45:51.740
And this was from... Willy... Billy...

388
00:47:07.452 --> 00:47:09.614
Hans says you have his sandals.

389
00:47:13.750 --> 00:47:15.411
We have to leave. Mutzi.

390
00:47:17.420 --> 00:47:18.455
Leave where?

391
00:47:18.880 --> 00:47:22.123
Here. We have to go. We're being transferred.

392
00:47:24.260 --> 00:47:26.592
Sorry. what?
-We're being transferred.

393
00:47:28.556 --> 00:47:30.672
To where?
-Oranienburg.

394
00:47:32.226 --> 00:47:33.216
What?

395
00:47:33.353 --> 00:47:36.766
They're swapping me for Arthur Liebehenschel.
He comes here.

396
00:47:38.066 --> 00:47:39.898
I take over as Deputy Inspector.

397
00:47:45.740 --> 00:47:49.779
If you've known this for a
while. why tell me now?

398
00:47:50.953 --> 00:47:53.866
There was no good moment to say it.
-You've said it now.

399
00:47:54.665 --> 00:47:56.872
Where are you going?
-To get the sandals.

400
00:48:00.380 --> 00:48:03.247
When did you find out?
-Pohl told me last week.

401
00:48:03.383 --> 00:48:04.965
I tried to make it go away.

402
00:48:11.474 --> 00:48:13.181
Then call Bormann.

403
00:48:13.643 --> 00:48:15.429
I've tried Bormann.

404
00:48:15.686 --> 00:48:17.973
Should I go to Hitler now?
-Well. yes.

405
00:48:20.775 --> 00:48:21.765
Rudolf.

406
00:48:28.699 --> 00:48:29.734
Rudolf.

407
00:48:31.911 --> 00:48:33.993
Don't turn your back on me.

408
00:48:35.665 --> 00:48:37.121
Stop.

409
00:48:37.250 --> 00:48:39.241
Calm down. Go back to the party.

410
00:48:42.380 --> 00:48:44.291
You can't do this to me.

411
00:48:50.221 --> 00:48:51.803
What is this? Marta.

412
00:48:54.058 --> 00:48:56.595
Mrs Höss?
-What's this. "Mrs Höss? Mrs Höss?"

413
00:48:56.727 --> 00:48:58.843
I'll show you Mrs Höss.
Mop it up.

414
00:48:59.605 --> 00:49:02.472
Don't forget you live well in our house.
Bloody hell.

415
00:49:04.152 --> 00:49:05.187
Now.

416
00:49:13.411 --> 00:49:14.776
Bloody hell.

417
00:50:14.096 --> 00:50:15.837
Why are they transferring you?

418
00:50:17.183 --> 00:50:18.799
Structural changes.

419
00:50:19.060 --> 00:50:20.221
What does that mean?

420
00:50:20.728 --> 00:50:23.937
They weren't specific.
But I'm not the only one being moved.

421
00:50:24.065 --> 00:50:25.476
There are lots of us.

422
00:50:29.195 --> 00:50:31.027
When?
-Soon.

423
00:50:31.155 --> 00:50:32.190
How soon?

424
00:50:32.323 --> 00:50:34.189
I'm waiting to be told.

425
00:50:42.083 --> 00:50:45.041
If it's about the investigation
they should call Himmler.

426
00:50:45.169 --> 00:50:47.376
He encouraged us.
-No.

427
00:50:49.006 --> 00:50:51.748
So it's not that?
-It's a political matter.

428
00:50:53.261 --> 00:50:55.423
Then go to Hitler.
-Don't be ridiculous.

429
00:50:55.555 --> 00:50:59.014
It's not ridiculous.
You're the one who carries out his orders

430
00:50:59.141 --> 00:51:00.723
once you peel away the layers.

431
00:51:01.018 --> 00:51:04.136
We have to face facts. We have to leave.

432
00:51:05.106 --> 00:51:07.723
No.
-You have to leave.

433
00:51:11.696 --> 00:51:12.686
Yes.

434
00:51:14.198 --> 00:51:16.235
Your work is in Oranienburg now.

435
00:51:16.367 --> 00:51:19.280
Mine is raising our children.

436
00:51:19.412 --> 00:51:20.902
and I'll do that from here.

437
00:51:26.294 --> 00:51:29.002
I never thought that you wouldn't be with me.

438
00:51:30.840 --> 00:51:32.171
Never crossed my mind.

439
00:51:33.009 --> 00:51:35.876
They'd have to drag me out of here.

440
00:51:36.929 --> 00:51:38.511
You know that.

441
00:51:42.810 --> 00:51:44.551
This is our home.

442
00:51:48.649 --> 00:51:51.232
We're living how we dreamed we would.

443
00:51:51.360 --> 00:51:54.398
Since we were 17. Beyond how we dreamed.

444
00:51:56.490 --> 00:51:58.072
Out of the city finally.

445
00:51:58.200 --> 00:52:00.817
Everything we want. On our doorstep.

446
00:52:01.245 --> 00:52:04.158
And our children are strong.
healthy and happy.

447
00:52:07.585 --> 00:52:10.703
Everything the Führer said
about how to live is how we do.

448
00:52:10.838 --> 00:52:12.420
Go East. Living space.

449
00:52:12.548 --> 00:52:13.959
This is our living space.

450
00:52:14.091 --> 00:52:15.547
This is our living space.

451
00:52:27.605 --> 00:52:29.562
I know you agree with me.

452
00:52:33.527 --> 00:52:37.236
Arthur can find somewhere else to live.
He doesn't need to take our home.

453
00:52:37.365 --> 00:52:40.483
You should make it a condition.
It's the least they can do.

454
00:52:42.912 --> 00:52:46.280
He'll want a townhouse. anyway.

455
00:52:50.544 --> 00:52:51.909
Rudolf?

456
00:52:54.799 --> 00:52:56.005
I heard you.

457
00:52:57.718 --> 00:52:58.833
So?

458
00:52:59.220 --> 00:53:00.506
I'll ask.

459
00:53:13.150 --> 00:53:15.016
You'll be working all the time.

460
00:53:15.152 --> 00:53:16.142
Yes.

461
00:53:16.946 --> 00:53:18.402
We'd never see you.

462
00:53:18.531 --> 00:53:19.566
No.

463
00:53:29.709 --> 00:53:31.996
I'll miss you. of course.

464
00:53:32.128 --> 00:53:34.119
But you'll come home when you can.

465
00:53:42.096 --> 00:53:43.586
I'll be...

466
00:53:44.682 --> 00:53:47.925
with you. Just like you'll be with me.

467
00:54:01.323 --> 00:54:02.484
Yes?

468
00:54:14.879 --> 00:54:16.461
And after the war

469
00:54:18.549 --> 00:54:20.631
when everything is over. we'll farm.

470
00:54:20.760 --> 00:54:22.467
Like we said.

471
00:55:02.176 --> 00:55:03.666
Do you all understand?

472
00:55:03.803 --> 00:55:05.043
Yes.

473
00:55:09.809 --> 00:55:12.096
So. I'll be missing your birthday.

474
00:55:15.731 --> 00:55:18.018
And maybe even our anniversary.

475
00:55:18.484 --> 00:55:20.521
Depending on how long I'll be gone.

476
00:55:22.488 --> 00:55:26.106
So. those are some of the things
that definitely add to the struggle.

477
00:55:28.118 --> 00:55:29.734
But the life we enjoy

478
00:55:31.247 --> 00:55:33.033
is very much worth the sacrifice.

479
00:55:36.961 --> 00:55:38.122
It's time for bed.

480
00:55:41.799 --> 00:55:43.961
Hans. your plate.

481
00:55:49.306 --> 00:55:50.341
Be calm.

482
00:57:44.296 --> 00:57:46.162
It'll be hard for you too.

483
00:57:47.967 --> 00:57:49.002
I know that.

484
00:57:50.511 --> 00:57:52.047
Don't you think I know that?

485
00:57:52.346 --> 00:57:53.381
I know that.

486
00:57:57.476 --> 00:57:58.466
I love you.

487
00:58:03.440 --> 00:58:05.226
I love you. my beauty.

488
00:58:17.454 --> 00:58:21.322
Call Walter Dürrfeld first thing and
see if he can join us at selection.

489
00:58:21.750 --> 00:58:23.582
Tell him they're Dutch

490
00:58:23.711 --> 00:58:25.497
and he can have his pick.

491
00:58:26.505 --> 00:58:28.837
Otherwise. I'll see him at the IG lunch.

492
00:58:31.010 --> 00:58:33.092
Letter to Messrs. Prüfer and Sander.

493
00:58:33.220 --> 00:58:34.255
Topf and Sons.

494
00:58:35.389 --> 00:58:37.346
Subject: New Crematorium.

495
00:58:39.143 --> 00:58:41.851
I'm glad you were able to
make the journey last week.

496
00:58:44.148 --> 00:58:47.231
SS-Obersturmbannführer
Bischoff and I both agree

497
00:58:47.359 --> 00:58:50.852
the ring crematorium is
definitely the answer.

498
00:58:52.489 --> 00:58:54.150
What a difference it will make.

499
00:58:54.491 --> 00:58:55.481
Bravo.

500
00:58:58.245 --> 00:58:59.656
I welcome your...

501
00:59:00.497 --> 00:59:02.204
I welcome your suggestion

502
00:59:02.583 --> 00:59:04.620
that the design should be patented

503
00:59:04.752 --> 00:59:07.084
in order to secure priority.

504
00:59:07.212 --> 00:59:09.419
I will follow up with a letter of intent.

505
00:59:11.633 --> 00:59:14.796
You should be aware.
I've been promoted to Deputy Inspector

506
00:59:14.928 --> 00:59:17.761
of concentration camps at the IKL.

507
00:59:18.182 --> 00:59:19.297
Come.

508
00:59:22.895 --> 00:59:25.478
And therefore. future communications

509
00:59:25.606 --> 00:59:27.688
will be from Oranienburg-Berlin.

510
00:59:30.110 --> 00:59:32.693
The focus there is now on lab our.

511
00:59:37.159 --> 00:59:40.322
Of course. this direction will affect our plans

512
00:59:43.540 --> 00:59:46.123
and though it pains me to leave Auschwitz

513
00:59:47.211 --> 00:59:51.170
I believe I'll be in a better position

514
00:59:52.299 --> 00:59:54.506
to push for funds and materials

515
00:59:55.469 --> 00:59:56.459
from there.

516
00:59:57.596 --> 00:59:58.927
Heil Hitler. Et cetera.

517
01:00:28.752 --> 01:00:30.914
Letter to Gruppenführer Glücks. IKL.

518
01:00:32.798 --> 01:00:33.959
Subject: Transfer.

519
01:00:36.218 --> 01:00:37.879
Dear Gruppenführer Glücks.

520
01:00:39.304 --> 01:00:42.842
I would like my family to remain

521
01:00:42.975 --> 01:00:46.388
at 88 Bielitzstrasse. KL Auschwitz

522
01:00:46.520 --> 01:00:48.477
for the duration of my transfer.

523
01:00:49.648 --> 01:00:51.514
It would be a great favour to me

524
01:00:51.650 --> 01:00:53.391
for this to be permitted.

525
01:00:54.319 --> 01:00:57.311
I must stress what a wonderful environment

526
01:00:57.447 --> 01:01:01.782
Hedwig is making for the
children since settling here.

527
01:01:02.870 --> 01:01:05.737
An inspiration in many ways

528
01:01:05.873 --> 01:01:08.911
for our new German community in the East.

529
01:01:09.793 --> 01:01:12.205
If this is acceptable.

530
01:01:12.713 --> 01:01:16.672
provision of a simple lodging for myself
in Oranienburg will suffice.

531
01:01:17.301 --> 01:01:20.760
I would be very grateful for a speedy answer.

532
01:01:20.888 --> 01:01:22.128
Heil Hitler. et cetera.

533
01:02:49.935 --> 01:02:51.141
Sweaty.

534
01:03:13.166 --> 01:03:16.204
The little snow white bird flew down
and sang.

535
01:03:18.046 --> 01:03:20.959
"Be warned. be warned."

536
01:03:25.846 --> 01:03:31.592
Gretel understood what the witch had in mind

537
01:03:33.061 --> 01:03:35.473
and said. "Please show me first.

538
01:03:35.605 --> 01:03:37.642
I don't know how to do that."

539
01:03:39.943 --> 01:03:42.651
The witch sat on the shovel

540
01:03:43.030 --> 01:03:44.816
and Gretel pushed her into the oven.

541
01:03:44.948 --> 01:03:48.157
as deep as she could.

542
01:03:50.078 --> 01:03:55.573
Then she closed the iron door of the oven.

543
01:03:56.084 --> 01:03:57.540
And secured it with a bar.

544
01:03:57.961 --> 01:04:01.170
The witch got cooked alive

545
01:04:02.174 --> 01:04:05.917
as a punishment for her horrible deeds.

546
01:04:07.596 --> 01:04:09.382
Gretel ran straight to Hansel.

547
01:04:11.224 --> 01:04:14.637
unlocked the goose cage and let him out.

548
01:04:16.104 --> 01:04:17.265
He jumped out

549
01:04:17.397 --> 01:04:19.604
and threw his arms around his sister's neck.

550
01:04:20.942 --> 01:04:24.310
They kissed one another.
cried with joy. and thanked God.

551
01:04:25.572 --> 01:04:27.154
The little white bird sang.

552
01:04:27.741 --> 01:04:31.951
"Pearls and gems for bread crumbs."

553
01:07:34.135 --> 01:07:36.001
[Polish] Here you are at last.

554
01:10:23.722 --> 01:10:25.713
Don't forget to stand straight.

555
01:10:32.188 --> 01:10:34.555
I've packed buttered bread for you all.

556
01:10:37.610 --> 01:10:38.941
Come on children. Hurry.

557
01:10:55.044 --> 01:10:56.034
Sophie.

558
01:11:07.474 --> 01:11:09.841
Tell her it's getting cold.

559
01:11:09.976 --> 01:11:11.011
She's not here.

560
01:11:11.436 --> 01:11:12.426
What?

561
01:11:12.937 --> 01:11:13.927
She's gone.

562
01:11:14.481 --> 01:11:15.846
What. not upstairs?

563
01:11:16.024 --> 01:11:17.139
No. she's gone.

564
01:11:17.525 --> 01:11:18.731
And her case has gone.

565
01:11:19.736 --> 01:11:21.101
That cannot be.

566
01:11:23.865 --> 01:11:24.855
Mum?

567
01:11:36.252 --> 01:11:37.742
Go and look for her.

568
01:12:36.855 --> 01:12:37.890
Aniela.

569
01:12:38.690 --> 01:12:39.646
Take it away.

570
01:12:41.484 --> 01:12:43.600
Was that here to spite me?

571
01:12:46.239 --> 01:12:47.729
No. Mrs. Höss.

572
01:13:00.670 --> 01:13:02.911
I could have my husband spread your ashes

573
01:13:03.047 --> 01:13:05.254
across the fields of Babice.

574
01:13:31.326 --> 01:13:33.283
Relax. let her find it.

575
01:13:37.582 --> 01:13:39.949
Are you not going to be a commandant anymore?

576
01:13:41.419 --> 01:13:44.002
I'll be head of all commandants.

577
01:13:45.298 --> 01:13:49.132
Inspecting their camps. seeing
where improvements can be made.

578
01:13:50.595 --> 01:13:53.212
Their yield. that kind of thing.

579
01:13:57.143 --> 01:13:59.180
It has a great name.

580
01:13:59.687 --> 01:14:02.395
It's girl's eye. or tickseed.

581
01:14:02.523 --> 01:14:05.811
Girl's eye?
-Girl's eye. yes.

582
01:14:05.944 --> 01:14:07.480
I can only guess

583
01:14:07.612 --> 01:14:11.150
that's because of its serrated petals.

584
01:14:11.282 --> 01:14:15.116
because they resemble the long eyelashes

585
01:14:15.244 --> 01:14:19.613
of women and girls.

586
01:16:08.024 --> 01:16:09.014
You there.

587
01:16:09.317 --> 01:16:10.398
Guard.

588
01:16:15.448 --> 01:16:16.529
Bring him here.

589
01:16:23.498 --> 01:16:24.613
What's he done?

590
01:16:24.874 --> 01:16:27.582
Fighting over an apple. Commandant.

591
01:16:28.252 --> 01:16:29.538
Drown him in the river.

592
01:16:30.797 --> 01:16:31.787
Come.

593
01:16:44.185 --> 01:16:46.301
Don't do that again.

594
01:16:51.192 --> 01:16:52.273
Move it.

595
01:16:53.986 --> 01:16:55.727
I don't care. Move it.

596
01:16:55.863 --> 01:16:57.024
Get it out.

597
01:17:06.582 --> 01:17:08.664
Are you going to stand there trembling?

598
01:17:10.670 --> 01:17:11.831
Something to say?

599
01:17:16.592 --> 01:17:17.582
Come.

600
01:17:56.132 --> 01:17:58.464
Aren't you lovely?

601
01:17:58.593 --> 01:18:00.800
Yes. you are lovely.

602
01:18:01.304 --> 01:18:02.840
Male or female?
-Male.

603
01:18:02.972 --> 01:18:04.838
How old?
-4 years old.

604
01:18:05.057 --> 01:18:06.593
What's his name?
-Torin.

605
01:18:09.353 --> 01:18:11.469
You don't see many with his colouring.

606
01:18:11.606 --> 01:18:13.688
No. mostly black or salt and pepper.

607
01:18:15.193 --> 01:18:18.185
I had a black one when I was little. EIsa.

608
01:18:18.321 --> 01:18:19.652
Born on the same day I was.

609
01:18:20.281 --> 01:18:21.692
He's lovely.
-Thank you.

610
01:18:22.491 --> 01:18:23.481
Come on.

611
01:18:24.285 --> 01:18:27.198
On Sunday at 19h there
will be a benefit concert

612
01:18:27.330 --> 01:18:30.368
at the Marksmen's Club to raise
money for War Winter Relief.

613
01:18:30.666 --> 01:18:34.705
Junior Squad Leader Johann Thißen will
conduct the orchestra in a two part program me

614
01:18:34.837 --> 01:18:36.794
featuring a tribute to Herms Niel...

615
01:18:37.256 --> 01:18:40.669
Liebehenschel. Auschwitz I.
Hartjenstein. Auschwitz ll <i>I</i> Birkenau.

616
01:18:40.801 --> 01:18:42.542
Schwarz. Auschwitz lll <i>I</i> Monowitz.

617
01:18:42.678 --> 01:18:45.045
Haas. Bergen-Belsen.
Pister. Buchenwald.

618
01:18:45.181 --> 01:18:47.263
Walter. Dachau.
Koegel. Flossenbürg.

619
01:18:47.558 --> 01:18:50.016
Hassebroek. Gross-Rosen.
Grünewald. Herzogenbusch.

620
01:18:50.144 --> 01:18:52.101
Sporrenberg. Hinzert.
Goecke. Kauen.

621
01:18:52.230 --> 01:18:54.346
Weiss. Majdanek.
Ziereis. Mauthausen.

622
01:18:54.482 --> 01:18:55.643
Dieter. Moringen.

623
01:18:55.775 --> 01:18:57.812
Hartjenstein. Natzweller-Struthof.

624
01:18:57.944 --> 01:18:59.855
Pauly. Neuengamme.
Göth. Plaszow.

625
01:18:59.987 --> 01:19:02.524
Suhren. Ravensbrück.
Kaindl. Sachsenhausen.

626
01:19:02.782 --> 01:19:04.022
Hoppe. Stutthof.

627
01:19:04.158 --> 01:19:06.490
Schnabel. Valvara.
Herbert. Warsaw.

628
01:19:07.203 --> 01:19:08.568
Apologies for absence.

629
01:19:08.704 --> 01:19:10.570
Förschner. Mittelbau-Dora.

630
01:19:10.706 --> 01:19:12.822
Sauer. Riga-Kaiserwald.

631
01:19:14.710 --> 01:19:19.420
The Führer has approved the deportation
of Hungary's 700.000 Jews for extermination

632
01:19:19.548 --> 01:19:21.880
and war production where able-bodied.

633
01:19:23.302 --> 01:19:26.465
An agreement was reached
with the new Hungarian government

634
01:19:26.597 --> 01:19:28.929
to begin the operation immediately.

635
01:19:29.642 --> 01:19:32.851
They are being amassed
for transportation to Auschwitz.

636
01:19:32.979 --> 01:19:35.186
4 trains a day. 3.000 on each.

637
01:19:35.314 --> 01:19:36.975
12.000 daily.

638
01:19:37.275 --> 01:19:39.482
Firstly via the Eastern zones. 1 to 3.

639
01:19:39.902 --> 01:19:42.234
Then via 4 and 5
in the middle of the country.

640
01:19:42.363 --> 01:19:44.229
and finally. Budapest.

641
01:19:45.700 --> 01:19:49.318
Pressburg and Vienna are heavily loaded
with military transports.

642
01:19:49.453 --> 01:19:51.410
Jewish transports will pass through

643
01:19:51.539 --> 01:19:53.530
Kassa and Muszyna instead.

644
01:19:54.500 --> 01:19:57.208
Based on estimates provided
by Obersturmbannführer Höss.

645
01:19:57.336 --> 01:20:00.419
25% will be retained for
lab our after selection.

646
01:20:00.548 --> 01:20:02.334
20% of those will be utilized

647
01:20:02.466 --> 01:20:04.457
in Auschwitz sub-camps.

648
01:20:04.593 --> 01:20:06.300
and the other 80%

649
01:20:06.429 --> 01:20:08.761
will come to your camps in due course.

650
01:20:10.266 --> 01:20:12.633
The scale is many times larger than before.

651
01:20:12.768 --> 01:20:14.429
So prepare yourselves.

652
01:20:14.895 --> 01:20:17.387
Before I hand over to
Obersturmbannführer Höss.

653
01:20:18.274 --> 01:20:20.811
I'd like to announce
the promotion of Colonel Maurer

654
01:20:20.943 --> 01:20:22.900
to the rank of SS-Standartenführer

655
01:20:23.029 --> 01:20:25.646
for consistently hitting his lab our targets.

656
01:20:25.781 --> 01:20:26.771
Bravo.

657
01:20:28.284 --> 01:20:32.118
I get fan mail from CEOs for this man.

658
01:20:32.413 --> 01:20:34.370
More famous than me.
-Thank you. sir.

659
01:20:34.957 --> 01:20:35.947
Well deserved.

660
01:20:36.083 --> 01:20:38.996
As I've said before.
I'm grateful for your leadership.

661
01:20:39.128 --> 01:20:41.745
Thank you. You have said that.
I appreciate that.

662
01:20:42.214 --> 01:20:43.955
Thank you. Obergruppenführer Pohl.

663
01:20:44.091 --> 01:20:45.957
Good morning. everyone.
-Good morning.

664
01:20:46.093 --> 01:20:47.675
Two apologies for absence.

665
01:20:47.803 --> 01:20:52.843
Sturmbannführer Förschner. Mittelbau-Dora.
Sturmbannführer Sauer. Riga-Kaiserwald.

666
01:20:53.392 --> 01:20:54.803
You will appreciate

667
01:20:54.935 --> 01:20:56.926
we have a very busy agenda today.

668
01:20:57.646 --> 01:20:59.853
The Hungarian operation is urgent.

669
01:20:59.982 --> 01:21:01.222
and complex.

670
01:21:01.359 --> 01:21:03.521
and will involve converging challenges

671
01:21:03.652 --> 01:21:05.984
at every operational level.

672
01:21:07.406 --> 01:21:09.818
Please turn to the first page in your files.

673
01:21:11.077 --> 01:21:12.738
You will see five headings.

674
01:21:13.454 --> 01:21:15.445
Item one. Timings.

675
01:21:15.581 --> 01:21:18.619
Item two.
Re-direction of construction resources.

676
01:21:18.751 --> 01:21:20.537
Item three. Transportation.

677
01:21:21.212 --> 01:21:23.078
For item four. prisoner workers.

678
01:21:23.214 --> 01:21:25.956
<i>Dr.</i> Meindl from Ste yr-Daimler-Puch.

679
01:21:26.092 --> 01:21:28.254
some of you know him. some of you don't.

680
01:21:28.969 --> 01:21:30.255
is joining us today

681
01:21:30.388 --> 01:21:33.221
to discuss pay rates and incentives.

682
01:21:33.891 --> 01:21:34.881
Item five.

683
01:21:35.017 --> 01:21:36.974
Fire and air defence measures.

684
01:22:40.207 --> 01:22:42.198
The girls didn't want to go out.

685
01:22:42.334 --> 01:22:43.324
Yes.

686
01:22:45.045 --> 01:22:46.501
Because it is so cold.

687
01:22:46.755 --> 01:22:49.793
Well. I love the snow.

688
01:23:03.272 --> 01:23:04.603
Stop.

689
01:23:04.690 --> 01:23:07.102
Leave me alone. Klaus.

690
01:23:16.327 --> 01:23:19.615
Stop it. Klaus.

691
01:23:22.291 --> 01:23:24.828
No.

692
01:23:27.630 --> 01:23:29.212
Leave me alone. you traitor.

693
01:23:40.476 --> 01:23:43.093
Saturday's funeral ceremony for the pupils

694
01:23:43.229 --> 01:23:44.685
of the Air Force School

695
01:23:44.855 --> 01:23:46.311
who died in the bombing raid

696
01:23:46.440 --> 01:23:48.226
of March 6th will start at 11 :30.

697
01:23:48.901 --> 01:23:51.017
SS pall bearers should congregate

698
01:23:51.153 --> 01:23:54.646
in the forecourt of the T Building by 10:45.

699
01:23:55.366 --> 01:23:58.700
Transport will leave for Hans Schemm School
promptly at 11 am.

700
01:23:59.662 --> 01:24:01.448
Commander of the Guard

701
01:24:02.289 --> 01:24:04.530
Obersturmbannführer Gustav Wegner

702
01:24:05.251 --> 01:24:07.367
will lead the cortège to the cemetery

703
01:24:08.170 --> 01:24:10.832
with a delegation from the
League of German Girls

704
01:24:11.423 --> 01:24:13.209
and Air Force Students.

705
01:24:19.306 --> 01:24:20.922
Obersturmbannführer Höss.

706
01:24:23.686 --> 01:24:25.017
Rudolf. Come on in.

707
01:24:25.646 --> 01:24:26.761
How are you?

708
01:24:26.981 --> 01:24:27.971
Good.

709
01:24:28.524 --> 01:24:30.811
I've just received this.

710
01:24:31.569 --> 01:24:34.527
Obergruppenführer Pohl met with
Reichsführer Himmler

711
01:24:34.655 --> 01:24:36.896
to assess the numbers involved

712
01:24:39.159 --> 01:24:40.741
and your name came up.

713
01:24:51.880 --> 01:24:53.996
We're moving Liebehenschel to Majdanek.

714
01:24:54.675 --> 01:24:57.508
He's not energetic enough for this.
-Okay.

715
01:24:57.636 --> 01:25:00.378
You'll receive operational orders
from Eichmann.

716
01:25:00.514 --> 01:25:01.504
Perfect.

717
01:25:01.640 --> 01:25:04.302
Tell me what resources you
need when you get there.

718
01:25:04.435 --> 01:25:05.425
I will.

719
01:25:05.561 --> 01:25:09.896
Any problems. come to me or Gerhard directly.

720
01:25:13.319 --> 01:25:14.309
Thank you.

721
01:25:14.778 --> 01:25:16.985
How's Hedwig?
-Good.

722
01:25:17.114 --> 01:25:21.199
Pohl told me she sends the boss
flowers from your garden every week.

723
01:25:21.327 --> 01:25:22.317
Yes.

724
01:25:23.579 --> 01:25:24.569
Get the job done.

725
01:25:25.122 --> 01:25:26.112
I will. Thank you.

726
01:25:26.624 --> 01:25:29.412
I appreciate the trust and confidence
you have in me.

727
01:25:40.346 --> 01:25:41.336
And?

728
01:25:43.766 --> 01:25:44.927
I'm not sure yet.

729
01:25:46.226 --> 01:25:47.341
Relax.

730
01:25:48.312 --> 01:25:50.394
He won't put them all up the chimney.

731
01:25:52.316 --> 01:25:54.148
You'll get your workers.

732
01:25:55.027 --> 01:25:56.108
You'll see.

733
01:26:09.041 --> 01:26:10.247
Are you sleeping okay?

734
01:26:10.376 --> 01:26:11.366
Yes.

735
01:26:13.754 --> 01:26:16.166
How many bowel movements
do you have per day?

736
01:26:16.548 --> 01:26:17.583
Twice per day.

737
01:26:18.676 --> 01:26:19.666
Urinating?

738
01:26:20.344 --> 01:26:21.550
Without issues.

739
01:26:23.305 --> 01:26:26.468
I'll feel around now. On the surface. first.

740
01:26:26.600 --> 01:26:30.184
If there is any pain.
then please let me know.

741
01:26:44.034 --> 01:26:45.024
This is Höss.

742
01:26:45.160 --> 01:26:48.949
Long-distance priority call.
KL Auschwitz. Höss private residence.

743
01:26:49.039 --> 01:26:50.154
I'll stay on the line.

744
01:27:05.597 --> 01:27:06.587
Are you there?

745
01:27:07.641 --> 01:27:09.427
Hello?
-Can you talk?

746
01:27:11.311 --> 01:27:13.018
Is everything okay?
-Yes.

747
01:27:13.147 --> 01:27:14.137
I have news.

748
01:27:14.273 --> 01:27:15.809
I told you I'd heard rumblings

749
01:27:15.941 --> 01:27:17.147
but nothing concrete.

750
01:27:18.235 --> 01:27:19.475
What news?

751
01:27:19.611 --> 01:27:20.692
The Hungary thing.

752
01:27:21.155 --> 01:27:23.271
The old man gave me orders from Heinrich.

753
01:27:23.615 --> 01:27:26.198
It's happening at last.
I'm coming back to run it.

754
01:27:26.326 --> 01:27:28.533
Well. I'm very relieved about that.

755
01:27:33.083 --> 01:27:35.074
I have to admit. I'm pleased as Punch.

756
01:27:37.880 --> 01:27:38.870
Yes.

757
01:27:40.966 --> 01:27:43.128
I don't know. I go to Budapest first.

758
01:27:43.260 --> 01:27:46.594
Things will be clearer after that.
Anyway. my cogs are turning.

759
01:27:46.722 --> 01:27:49.384
I must get on.
I'll call you later. after the party.

760
01:27:49.516 --> 01:27:50.847
No. Wait. please.

761
01:27:50.976 --> 01:27:52.466
Tell Eleanor Pohl.

762
01:27:53.103 --> 01:27:54.593
when she receives her parcel.

763
01:27:54.730 --> 01:27:56.061
to look in the compact.

764
01:27:56.190 --> 01:27:57.225
They're inside.

765
01:31:17.683 --> 01:31:20.220
I heard Himmler's calling it Operation Höss.

766
01:31:20.477 --> 01:31:22.639
That's fantastic. I'm so happy for you.

767
01:31:22.980 --> 01:31:23.970
Thank you. Mutzi.

768
01:31:24.106 --> 01:31:25.187
It's your name too.

769
01:31:26.024 --> 01:31:27.139
Who was there?

770
01:31:27.943 --> 01:31:29.183
To tell you the truth

771
01:31:29.444 --> 01:31:31.526
I wasn't really paying attention.

772
01:31:32.280 --> 01:31:35.523
I was too busy thinking
how I'd gas everyone in the room.

773
01:31:36.034 --> 01:31:39.777
Very difficult. logistically.
because of its high ceiling.

774
01:31:42.374 --> 01:31:44.331
It's the middle of the night

775
01:31:44.459 --> 01:31:46.871
and I need to be in bed.

776
01:31:48.046 --> 01:31:49.832
I shouldn't have called so late.

777
01:31:50.298 --> 01:31:52.335
I was just excited to tell you the name.

778
01:31:53.135 --> 01:31:55.968
You can tell me about it when you get back.

779
01:32:03.770 --> 01:32:05.977
You have told them Daddy's coming home?

780
01:32:07.524 --> 01:32:08.605
Yes.

781
01:32:08.734 --> 01:32:09.769
Goodnight.
